Never giving up on one’s passion and dream is no doubt one of the ways to keep hope alive and with the assurance that the big break is just by the corner For Mistikay who is  fondly known as Kayode Afolabi Ajayi, being committed to making good music and not giving up on his dream of being recognized in the music industry is what has brought him this far in his career. The singer and songwriter who started his journey into the music world in 2009 while having his National Diploma at Federal Polytechnic Ado-Ekiti was very popular among his peers in school days and enjoyed the support from those around him. He however stopped writing music, due to the lack of funding to further his career to the next level. Despite the setback he faced, Mistikay has proven beyond doubt that giving up is not a part of him by releasing a new song entitled “Nawa O”. The new track which was released on Jan 17 was produced by Prodigy Beats and mastered by Lord Gabriel has so far received positive reviews as well as air plays that has kept his fans impressed and vibing to the new sound. Mistikay while recounting his experience,  spoke about how he has been able to get back into the music business and his readiness to wow his fans in the coming months. “The song is just a proof that when you don’t give up on your dreams, there’s no limit to what you can do or achieve. I experienced a set back at one time, but it only pushed me further to achieving my dreams and here I am today.I’m back like I never left and I’ll want my fans to know that we’re just getting started, “ he said.